 riddles lies at the core of the development of Persian poetry. It proposes a careful, learned and systematic analysis of this hitherto little-studied and puzzling poetical game.’Christine van Ruymbeke, University of Cambridge  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aPersian literaturexHistory and criticismx747-1500. 0aPersian literaturey747-1500xHistory and criticism. 0aRiddles in literature. 4aAsian Studies. 4aLIT. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Persian.2bisacsh  apoetry, riddles, metaphors, Persian literature, 10th-12th century, literary description, Iran.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978940060010240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789400600102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789400600102/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK